One person was killed in a heavy mudslide at an informal settlement in Umlazi, Durban. On Sunday, Medi Response paramedics responded to reports of a heavy mudslide affecting residential dwellings in the south-east township. “It was established that a landslide had occurred, engulfing an informal dwelling. The single occupant of the dwelling was unfortunately killed during the landslide,” said Medi Response in a statement. Search and rescue units combed the area and found no one else was injured. Heavy rains have been falling throughout KwaZulu-Natal over the weekend and into Monday. Robert McKenzie, KZN Emergency Medical Services spokesperson has warned motorists to drive slow and be vigilant on the roads.